In this statement, the President expresses gratitude to Chairman Julius Genachowski for his service at the Federal Communications Commission (FCC). The President acknowledges Genachowski's focus on promoting innovation, supporting businesses in a global economy, and attracting future industries and jobs. Under Genachowski's leadership, high-speed internet access has been expanded, the mobile sector has experienced growth, and the open internet has been protected as a platform for entrepreneurship and free speech. The President thanks Genachowski for his service and friendship and wishes him the best of luck.